For example, if I have a vertical split of two windows as the left child of a horizontal split, I can't mouse-resize the divider of the horizontal split from within the nested vertical split, but I can resize it from the single window on the other side. This should be made clearer by the following diagram where `O` designates where I'm clicking:

    




             +-------------------------+-----------------------+
             |                         |                       |
             | +---------------------+ |                       |
             | |                     | |                       |
             | |    This doesn't--&gt;O | |  O&lt;--This works       |
             | |                     | |                       |
             | +---------------------+ |                       |
             | |                     | |                       |
             | |                     | |                       |
             | |                     | |                       |
             | |                     | |                       |
             | +---------------------+ |                       |
             |                         |                       |
